The Economic Freedom Fighters (EFF) wants the National Council of Provinces to pass a resolution on the closure of schools due to the rising number of COVID-19 cases. The EFF has brought a notice for such a motion to be debated and resolved to close the schools. Gauteng and the Northern Cape are among the two provinces which had seen a rising number of COVID-19 infections among learners recently. EFF member of the National Council of Provinces (NCOP) Mmabatho Mokause brought the notice at the NCOP virtual sitting on Wednesday. Mmabatho Mokause on the calling for the closure of schools: In the video below, EFF calls for the closure of schools:  